# Ship Flight

SC-style IFCS: mouse aim + nose lag, mass-scaled thrust/torque. **Flight is not Rapier** — Rapier is deck/station walking only.

## Before changing feel

1. Read `.cursor/skills/ship-flight/SKILL.md` (presets, symptom → fix, workflow).
2. Read AGENTS.md section **Ship flight (SC-style IFCS)**.

## Ownership

| Layer | Where |
| --- | --- |
| Per-ship stats | `ship-controller` on hull → `ShipSpec` via `ship_runtime.ts` |
| Global IFCS / damping | `src/flight/flight_config.ts` (all ships) |
| Integrate | `flight_body.ts` (+ sandbox flat env) |
| Aim / PD IFCS | `flight_aim.ts` + `player_controls.ts` |
| Main play | `game_loop.ts` `MODE_IN_SHIP` |
| Preview | `ship_play_session.ts` pilot mode |
| HUD | `flight_reticle.ts` (aim + nose pips); `cockpit_gaze_hud.ts` (Hold F look-at labels); `cockpit_speed_hud.ts` (cockpit-stat speed) |
| Cockpit controls | `cockpit-control` markers → `ShipLayout.cockpitControls` → `cockpit_gaze.ts` |
| Cockpit instruments | `cockpit-stat` markers → `ShipLayout.cockpitStats` → `cockpit_stats.ts` + speed HUD |

## Rules of thumb

- Balance **one hull** via inspector mass/thrust/torque — do not edit `FLIGHT_CONFIG` unless every ship is wrong.
- Pitch bounce → ↑ `AIM_IFCS_DAMPING` or ↓ pitch torque / max angular rate (see skill).
- **No airborne gravity** (Star Wars hover) and **no auto-level** — roll/pitch stick; do not reintroduce without an explicit design change.
- `world/` / `flight/` must not import `three` or DOM.
- Keep flight math out of `render/` and out of Rapier.

Deeper tuning: `.cursor/skills/ship-flight/SKILL.md`. Prefab authoring: `.cursor/skills/prefab-editor/SKILL.md`.
